nodes.title: Tiled Diffusion Info
widgets_values:
üîß Tiled Diffusion ‚Äì Key Parameters

| Parameter         | Description                                                                 |
|-------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `tile_size`       | Width & height of each tile. Recommended: 512, 768, 1024.                   |
|                   | üîπ 512 ‚Äì safest, low VRAM                                                    |
|                   | üîπ 768 ‚Äì fast, stable, great for portraits                                   |
|                   | üîπ 1024 ‚Äì high detail, but can add "extra stuff" & takes longer              |
| `tile_overlap`    | Pixels shared between tiles. Prevents seams. Use 32‚Äì128 based on tile size. |
|                   | üîπ 32 for 512 tiles, 64 for 768, 128 for 1024                                |
| `tile_batch_size` | Tiles processed at once. Higher = faster, but uses more VRAM.               |
|                   | üîπ 1‚Äì2 = safe and clean                                                      |
|                   | üîπ 4‚Äì6 = fast on 24GB GPUs (like RTX 4090)                                   |

üí° Tips:
- Use **square tiles** (width = height)
- Match **overlap** to tile size to avoid seams
- 768 is often the sweet spot for quality + speed
- 1024 tiles may generate more detail, but also more "creative noise"
